This paper involves the analysis of a social network and its impact on the Web's information ecosystem, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also involves the analysis of hate speech, which could fall under the categories of cybercrime (cs.CR) or computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of user behavior and community evolution, which could fall under the categories of social computing (cs.SOC) or computer and society (cs.CY).
